				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				Might as well add my story, cause I do have stuff to add.  was just gonna pay the 2k on Luclin to buy it, knew this bear was hard to bag....but I had just twinked the shammie out a bit, and felt like playing her anyway, so's I jog up to Halas and practice, oh and had to fish for awhile to get somes scales, no vendor had any, then head out to the cave run straight east of megan's tower, and you see a hole right below you, can't miss it!!  But you can get there from any hole as long as you have EB.<BR>
Apex guy in there when I got there, as I run past him he /ooc please don't kill Miragul<BR>
boy did I laugh /ooc hoping to avoid him at all cost, lvl 29  B)<BR>
I talked to him later and he said Miragul is PH for bear....and that night I was beginning to believe it so, <BR>
**because**<BR>
I killed the roaming skele the minute I got in there, dodged Miragul a few times, whacked the skele, and gated back to the entrance where had bound myself.  set the timer 4 hours.  WELL, 4 hours came and went, and NOTHING spawned not even Ice bone, Miragul had been dead about 2 hours at this time.  I was so tired I was fell alseep a few times, so I gave it up, logged on the next day, and first thing I did was cast sense animal, and I choked when I saw a glacier bear, took a quick &quot;c&quot;  blue at 29, so I charged in, buffs we're new from last night, I was ready to go.  Ran into a high lvl cleric inside, crossed my fingers that he wasn't there for the same reason, and kept searching.  Ran into him finally, this sucker is huge, out weighs Iceberg by at least a ton (theoretically speaking)<BR>
So I did what i do best, and panicked.  Had to get my husband to step in when I got him half dead cause I was shaking so hard I couldn't control the mouse  lol.  I was just floored that I caught him, and now don't have to pay 2k for one  hehe.  But I soloed him easily enough at 29, specially if he was 28, that's a nice bag.  Hits for 54.<BR>
<BR>
BUT, getting to my point, others have said here that the bear and Miragul can be up together, one said two bears were up, and I can confirm that in my blind dash around those caves today I ran past an ice bone, and remember making an effort to get around him without agroing so I didnt have to waste time with it.<BR>
<BR>
So, may not have a PH at all, or could be 2 spawns....Ice bone PH for each, that would explain why bear and icebone up together, bear and Miragul up together, and icebone and Miragul up together..... if Miragul had been up today I would have surely been toast. I was running around like a chicken with my head cut off, trying to find that bear.<BR>
<BR>
anyway, hope this makes hope for Glacier bear campers, also, the cave isn't hard to learn if you run around it for a couple hours, there is a big outter loop, run down one way and eventually you get back to entrance, and then all the middle tunnels make either circles too, or connect to outter loop, kinda hard to explain, but it's circles.  If ya go in and make right turns everytime you can make one until you can't anymore it dead-ends at a house with 3 icebones, and some wizzie quest rod in middle, seen another one of those in Neriak getting my old silver coin for tashania quest.<BR>
<BR>
Miragul sees through invis...obviously... so don't think invising and running around is any safer than just running in, but the other guy doesn't.  Didn't mess with his gobbie though, little too chicken.<BR>
<BR>
Hope ya bag yer bear!!
