				ok heres my experience how i got the glacier bear pelt.<BR>
Yesterday, 2/5/01, looked all the comments of the totemic helm from this site and maximumeq.com. After reading all the comments, seems all are the same, kill the wandering ph skelly, watchout for lich, wait for about 8-12 hrs of spawn time. Coz im too shady to buy 3k helm i decided to camp it.<BR>
after night school, i log my shaman, and went to the underwater cave. its 10:45 pm , killed a gazillion of ice bone skellies, what the heck, it might trigger to spawn the bear or the wandering ph skellie, at 11pm i saw a wandering ph skellie near the house (not the hut) killed it and assumed after 7-8 hours bear will spawn. thats what i heard from comments. Made me more confident camping the bear. I keep ooc im camping the bear so noone will bother. Since i got work and school the next day, need sleep, so i slept from time to time, waking every hour, killing ice bone skellies, use sense animals, wander around if there is another wandering ph skelli. 2am still no luck, i was planning on waking on 6am so it would be 7 hours from kiling the wandering ph skellie from 11 pm. but i was not sure, it might spawn anytime. at 3 am another ph skellie wanders in the middle of the cave almost near suloc, killed it, sense, no luck. Then the exciting part, i woke up again at 6 am, sow myself, uv , then sense animal, guess what, glacier bears pops up. I tracked the bear using sense animal and it was goin near the hut. look around if lich i there, nope, pet attack, vos, scourge, what ya got, a dead glaciar bear. looted the pelt. sleep some more, then i went to work. <BR>
i think the bear spawns randomly anywhere (this time i think it spawn in the middle of cave), but wanders the corridor near suloc, the house, and the hut. i think killing a ph skellie then wait like 7-8 hours is true, but ill try to do it again to make it sure its true. Cant wait to get my helm, saved me 3kpp. info of other ingredients is a banded helm(medium), ogreskin chamois (CT), and a dufrenite(forgot if its crush,powdered, etc.)  just read some of the comments here for the dufrenite. hope my experience help u guys out there. It really feels good to gain something from hard work.<BR>
